CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 13, 1963, pg. 5 reads: "Negro Job Discussion - With the Urban League's Ed Smith (back to camera) as one of the spokesmen, "operation Think" members told the East Liberty Chamber of Commerce that the Negro community wants jobs in that area's stores. Shown in the picture are (extreme left bloc, seated and standing, left to right) Mrs. Mayme Tibbs and Mrs. Wendell Silvers, Bill Paige and the Rev. B.F. McFadden, all of "Operation Think", and East Liberty Chamber of Commerce members (standing) Bryce Wallace, moderator; Mrs. Dorothy Brown, Joseph L. Schlosser, Bill Dinsmore, John Bartoletti and (seated) Ray Waples, Robert Haas and Robert Whitehill. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of "Operation Think" and East Liberty Chamber of Commerce members, from left, seated: Mayme Tibbs, Mrs. Wendell Silvers, Ray Waples, Robert Haas, and Robert Whitehill; standing: Bill Paige, Rev. B.F. McFadden, Bryce Wallace, Dorothy Brown, Joseph L. Schlosser, Bill Dinsmore, and John Bartoletti, gathered around conference table in interior
